<HTML>
<head><title>Letter from Al -- NR</title></head>
<BODY>
<CENTER><H2>Letter from Al</H2></CENTER>
<HR>
25-September-1995

<P>

<P>
I've loaded up Windows 95 and I'm multi-tasking like crazy! I've
got some campaign e-mail on one screen, Tipper's all-fiber diet
on another, and an article for the Washington Post -- it's about
people in New York City who steal other people's recyclables.
I'm e-mailing it to you right now. All I've got to do is double-click
on the MSN icon . . . here goes . . .
<P>
FOCUS GROUP #19 8/27/95 BEST WESTERN INN -- LAKE HAVASU, ARIZONA.
PARTICIPANTS: Bill, 47, white male; Otis, 64, white male; Marjorie,
34, black female; Dakotah, 23, white female; Keith, 42, black
male; Dakota, 25, white male.
<P>
MODERATOR: Well, first, let me thank you all for coming here --

<P>
DAKOTA: Where's my 25 bucks, hosehead?
<P>
MODERATOR: If I could just -- 
<P>
MARJORIE: Are my kids okay outside?
<P>
MODERATOR: I'm handing out some pages -- 
<P>
OTIS: No one -- that's NO ONE, Sunny Jim -- is taking away my
Medicare.
<P>
MARJORIE: I'm going to check on my kids.
<P>
MODERATOR: Well, we're not really talking about Medicare today.
If I could direct your attention -- 
<P>
OTIS: Damn right we're not talking about Medicare, because NO
ONE is going to take it away.
<P>
DAKOTA: Twenty-five bucks, doofoid.
<P>
DAKOTAH: Can you let the man talk, please?
<P>
MODERATOR: Thanks. What I'd like to talk about is your feelings
about Bill Clinton and Al Gore.
<P>
OTIS: Hate 'em. Hate 'em both. And that wife of his tried to steal
my Medicare.
<P>
MODERATOR: Um . . . okay, we'll start with Otis. Otis, you say
that you quote hate unquote Bill Clinton and Al Gore -- 
<P>
OTIS: And his wife.
<P>
MODERATOR: Whose wife?
<P>
OTIS: Clinton's wife. The Medicare thief.
<P>
MODERATOR: And so you'd describe yourself as someone who is .
. . what? Conservative? Liberal?
<P>
OTIS: I'd describe myself as someone who's entitled to Medicare.
<P>
MODERATOR: Okay, moving right along. Bill, you've been awfully
quiet.
<P>
BILL: That's due to my incredible, simmering rage.
<P>
MODERATOR: I see. And to whom do you direct your rage?
<P>
BILL: My wife.
<P>
MODERATOR: I mean in a political sense.
<P>
BILL: Still her.
<P>
MODERATOR: Let me be more specific. Are you angry because as a
white middle-aged man you feel that your place in society is eroding,
and that the general lawlessness of the streets has come to make
you feel like an outsider in your own country?
<P>
BILL: Well, I wasn't before you mentioned it, but, wow, I see
your point. I am so freaking angry!
<P>
DAKOTAH: Then join a militia, Nazi man!
<P>
BILL: What?
<P>
DAKOTAH: I know all about you angry white men! My dad is one!
At first he was real nice and real supportive and then when I
changed my name to Dakotah and got my nose pierced he was like,
a crazy man. So full of rage. I reject that rage.
<P>
MODERATOR: Dakotah, how would you describe your politics?
<P>
DAKOTAH: I wouldn't.
<P>
MODERATOR: You mean you can't describe your feelings?
<P>
DAKOTAH: No, I mean that you probably work for the government
which killed Kennedy and Malcolm X and if I told you what I really
believe you'd have me killed just like you killed Jerry Garcia.
<P>
MODERATOR: Keith . . . how about you?
<P>
KEITH: Oh, am I here?
<P>
MODERATOR: Excuse me?
<P>
KEITH: The black man always goes last.
<P>
MODERATOR: I was going clockwise.
<P>
KEITH: To you, clockwise. To me, a systematic method of silencing
my voice.
<P>
MODERATOR: I'm terribly sorry.
<P>
KEITH: You think that white man is angry? Check under my hood
sometime.
<P>
BILL: Are you saying that you're angrier than me?
<P>
KEITH: Damn right I am.
<P>
BILL: I'm WAY angrier than you.
<P>
KEITH: Oh yeah?
<P>
BILL: Yeah.
<P>
KEITH: Rodney King!
<P>
BILL: O.J. walks!
<P>
KEITH: Mark Fuhrman!
<P>
BILL: Gangsta rap!
<P>
MODERATOR: Gentlemen! Please! All I want to know is how you would
describe yourselves politically.
<P>
KEITH: Angry. I'd describe myself as angry.
<P>
BILL: Me too.
<P>
OTIS: You know what I think.
<P>
MODERATOR: Yes, I think I can recall. Thank you all for coming.
<P>
FOCUS GROUP #19 COMPLETED. 
</BODY>

</HTML>
