<P><center>
<H2>Next: Literacy</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
<blockquote>





	"Graduates get degrees, but do they know how to get an apartment? Workshops come to the rescue. Roger Williams University in Bristol, R.I., covers basics like budgeting and finding a place to live in 'Reality 101.'
	"Social skills are on the syllabus, too. Texas Christian University in Fort Worth has a seminar that includes a six-course dinner with practice ordering wine. Meanwhile, Saint Mary's College, Notre Dame, Ind., titles a talk Grace Under Pressure: Your Guide to Professional Etiquette.'
	"Susquehanna University in Selinsgrove, Pa., invites local business executives to a dinner where students practicing introducing themselves."

Pamela Sebastian, <I>Wall Street Journal</I>, December 26, 1996
</blockquote>
