<P><center>
<H2>For $750, The Choice Is Yours</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
<blockquote>




	"You'll still have to buy them, but you can have them turned off.
<P>
	"This is the concession that the National highway Traffic Safety Administration proposed last month, in response to growing public alarm over the risks posed by air bags to children. To date, more than 30 children have been killed by air-bag deployment, many of them in low-speed accidents, and there is mounting evidence that these devices may endanger certain adults as well. The children's deaths are not merely a tragic side effect; air bags kill more kids under age 10 than they save."
<P>
Sam Kazman, <I>Wall Street Journal</I>, December 3, 1996


</blockquote>
<!------------------------------------------------------------>
