<P>
<center>
<H1>
<B>Web Browser Information</B>
</H1>
</center>
<font size=4>
<p>The Senior Information Network is best viewed with a web browser that supports HTML
version 2 syntax (i.e. Netscape, Prodigy, Microsoft Network, etc). Such features as HTML tables are used to provide easy to read pages.
<p>
The Webmasters at the Senior-<i>Inet</i> are doing everything possible to make this system compatible with all web browsers, but some systems may not be in full compliance with HTML version 2 standards.
<p>
<font size=3>
Note: America online users have the option to utilize either the Netscape browser or the
Microsoft Network browser, which offers enhanced Web browsing capabilities. Please
click <A HREF="./aolconvt.htm">here</a> to find detailed instructions on how to convert your  <A HREF="./aolconvt.htm">America Online browser.</a> This is a free upgrade for AOL users.
<p>
CompuServe also provides their subscribers with access to Netscape's browser. Access CompuServe help for detailed instructions for using the Netscape browser.
