<img border=0 width=350 height=50
SRC="./graphics/sifnlogo.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
<HR SIZE=4>
<!-- Generation of PM publication page 1 -->
<center>
<H1>Senior Banking Directory</H1>
</center>
Senior Banking now starts with free checking accounts, free checks and free notary service, as well as the old stand-by Trust Department. Now with changes in securities regulations, more banks have set up insurance and securities departments. Some banks also go the one step further for seniors and do things like seminars on topics of interest to seniors, luncheons and trips for seniors only.
<P>
<center>
<IMG SRC="./graphics/swash4.gif"><BR>
</center>
<P>This page is designed to allow you to read/print articles on Senior Banking; and to let you explore banking services offered in various cities.
<h4> 
<B>Senior Banking Articles:</B>
</h4>
</h4>
<ul>
<LI>
<A HREF="./articles/bank1.htm">What does your bank cost? It pays to check</A>
<BR>
<p>
<LI>
<A HREF="./articles/bank2.htm">Gloria Francis helps seniors and her bank
<BR>
<p>
<LI>
<A HREF="./articles/bank3.htm">Banks can fight fraud against seniors</A>
<BR>
</ul>
<P>
<h3><center>Select your city for Senior Banking info from below...</center></h3>

<table>
<td><a href="cospbank.htm">Colorado Springs, CO  </a></td>
<td><a href="denbank.htm">Denver, CO  </a></td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
<td><a href="monubank.htm">Monument, CO </a></td>
</table>

