SRC="./graphics/sifnlogo.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
<HR SIZE=4>

<!-- Generation of PM publication page 1 -->
<P>
<center>
<H1>
<B>Senior Housing Directory</B>
</H1>
</center>
Senior Housing now encompasses a wide spectrum of options. These include Independent Housing, Assisted Living, and Skilled Care. 
<BR><BR>
<fonts=5><b>Independent Housing</b><fonts=3><br>
Approximately 85% of seniors presently live in what is referred to as Independent Housing,
i.e. their own homes or apartments, and often with at least one relative. 
There are also many independent living facilities that are exclusively &quot;senior&quot; or 
55+, to provide an independent living setting that excludes younger families.
<BR><BR>
<fonts=5><b>
Assisted Living</b><fonts=3><br>
The next basic step in Senior Housing is called Assisted Living. These 
are facilities designed to provide services for their residents such as 
medication monitoring, transportation and meal preparation because these residents 
need closer supervision than that provided in independent living situations, but 
they don't require 24-hour skilled nursing care.
<BR><BR>
<fonts=5><b>
Skilled or Long Term Care</b><fonts=3><br>
The third basic category of senior living is called Skilled Care or Long 
Term Care. Long term is perhaps a misnomer because most of these facilities 
are tuned into rehabilitation programs nowadays. We used to call them 
nursing homes, but now they are better named as Skilled Care Facilities.
<BR><BR>
<fonts=5><b>
Alzheimer's Care</b><fonts=3><br>
To these basic categories we have added Alzheimers Care because of it's specialized importance in Senior Housing continuum of care.
<P>
<center>
<IMG SRC="./graphics/swash4.gif"><BR>
</center>
<P>This page is designed to allow you to view, read and/or print 
articles specifically related to Housing; and to allow you to browse your way to 
Senior Housing via a  City Page, and then individual Web Pages for Senior 
Housing Facilities. 
<h4>
<B>Senior Housing Articles:</B>
</h4>
<ul>
<LI>
<A HREF="./articles/hous1.htm">Continuum of Care</A>
--<i>Description of services that a facility may offer</i><BR>
<p>
<LI>
<A HREF="./articles/hous2.htm">Beware of Unscrupulous Groups</A>
--<i>Protecting seniors from unscrupulous visitors</i><BR>
</ul>
<P>
<h3><center>Select your city for Senior Housing info from below...</center></h3>
