<center>
<H1>BANKING PAGE</H1>
<H3>Colorado Springs, Colorado</H3>
<img border=0 width=350 height=200
<IMG SRC="./graphics/cospp1.jpg" ALT="[picture]" ALIGN=center><BR>

</center>

<!-- Generation of PM publication page 1 -->


<P>Nestled at the foot of Pikes Peak, Colorado Springs is the second largest city in Colorado.It has a metropolitan population of just over 400,000 people, with approximately 75,000 of them being 50+.The number one attraction is the U. S. Air Force Academy and its famous Cadet Chapel. The number one photo op is The Garden of the Gods with Pikes Peak in the background.
<P>The best full-resource for seniors currently available is through:
<font size=2>
<center>
          Pikes Peak Area Agency on Aging
<BR> Senior Information & Referral Service
<BR>                       15 South 7th Street
 <BR>                     Colorado Springs, CO 80905
<BR>                        Phone (719) 471-2096  Fax (719) 471-1226 
<font size=3>
</center>
<P>In the works is a Senior Resource Database which will be available soon from the Pikes Peak Library District - stay tuned!
<P>
<center>
<IMG SRC="./graphics/swash4.gif"><BR>
</center>
<P>From here visit Colorado Springs area Senior Banking Web Pages for: <p>
