<HTML>

<HEAD>
<title>Oregon Welcomes You! - Help</title>
</HEAD>

<BODY>
<a href="index.htm"><img align=bottom src="gifs/tico.gif" border=0 alt="Oregon Welcomes You!"></a>

<img align=bottom src="gifs/help.gif" height=50 border=0 alt="back"><p>

Welcome to <strong>Oregon Welcomes You!</strong><p>

<strong>Oregon Welcomes You!</strong> has been developed to make it easy for you to find online information on Oregon.  This help section hopefully will answer some of your questions about how to get around in <strong>Oregon Welcomes You!</strong>.  If you still have questions you can <a href="mailto: webmaster@tico.org">send e-mail to our resident expert</a>, fax your question to Oregon Welcomes You! at 503-393-3040 or call for information at 503-393-3535, Monday through Friday from 9 AM to 5 PM PST.<p>

To return to this page from anywhere in <strong>Oregon Welcomes You!</strong>, <p>
click on this button: <img align=middle src="gifs/tico.gif" alt="Oregon Welcomes You!"> and then click on the word Help at the bottom of the page.

<hr>

<h2>Getting Around in <strong>Oregon Welcomes You!</strong></h2>

At the top of each page in <strong>Oregon Welcomes You!</strong> you will find the <strong>Oregon Welcomes You!</strong> logo and the title of the section you are in.<p>

Here's what you would see at the top of the page in the Visitor Industry Awareness section:<p>

<strong>Example:</strong><p>

<img align=bottom src="gifs/tico.gif" border=0 alt="Oregon Welcomes You!">

<img align-bottom src="gifs/visitor.gif" alt="Visitor Industry Awareness Campaign">
<p>

Depending on what browser you are using, your location should also be displayed at the top of the window.<p>

<strong>Example:</strong><p>

The message at the top of this window should say:<p>
<center>"Oregon Welcomes You! - Help"</center><p>

<h2>Links, Buttons, and other Gadgets</h2>

The primary way of getting around in <strong>Oregon Welcomes You!</strong> or any web page is through links.  Different browsers display links in different ways.  <p>

<h3>Links</h3>
The most common way to indicate a link is by highlighting text in blue and underlining it.<p>

<strong>Example:</strong>  See below to see how your browser highlights links.<p>


<a href="index.htm">This link takes you to the <strong>Oregon Welcomes You!</strong> home page.</a><p>


To follow the link you simply click on the highlighted words with your mouse.  (Note: text-based browsers follow links by pressing return or the right arrow key.)<p>

<h3>Buttons</h3>

In addition to using text links, <strong>Oregon Welcomes You!</strong> also uses graphic links called "buttons."  You follow a button by clicking on the graphic.<p>

<strong>Example:</strong><p>

Click on this button to go to the<strong> Oregon Welcomes You!</strong> home page:<p>
<a href="index.htm"><img align=bottom src="gifs/tico.gif" border=0 alt="Oregon Welcomes You!"></a><p>

<strong>Example:</strong><p>

This button will take you to the <i>Oregon Directory</i> page:<p>

<a href="directry.htm"><img align=bottom src="gifs/directry.gif" border=0 alt="Oregon Directory!"></a><p>
</BODY><p>

To follow graphic links you simply click on the graphic or button with your mouse.  (Note: In <strong>Oregon Welcomes You!</strong> text-based browsers display graphic links as text.)  The only time a button isn't linked to a page is when you're already at that page.

<hr>


<h2>To begin your exploration of <i>Oregon Welcomes You!</i>, follow this link:</h2>
<p>
<center> <a href="index.htm"><img align=middle src="gifs/tico.gif" border=0 alt="Oregon Welcomes You!"> </a> </center>
<p>

<p>
<hr>

<a href="mailto:webmaster@tico.org"><i>webmaster@tico.org</i></a>
</HTML>
























