<br><HR>
<H1>The Travel Industry Council of Oregon</H1>

<P>
The Travel Industry Council of Oregon is a non-profit, state-wide
visitor industry association comprised of all private sector segments
representing the visitor industry in Oregon.
<P>
The organization is funded through membership subscriptions, grants
and special events.  In the past, it had principally served as
a lobbying agency for the Oregon Tourism Division, and been active
in legislative affairs.  Beginning in 1995, the association embraced
a much broader role as the private sector partner of the new Oregon
Tourism Commission (formerly Oregon Tourism Division).  After
successfully securing a Key Industries grant, the Council took
over the Visitor Industry Awareness campaign from the Commission.
 Other projects include linking the industry electronically, managing
the industry Workforce 2000 program, and continuing its legislative
lobbying efforts.
<P>
Future plans call for the Council to become fully independent
from the Oregon Lodging Association with separate offices and
paid staff to manage the ongoing activities and programs of the
association.  It will also be responsible for soliciting and securing
long-term funding for its own sustainability and for funding the
public/private account designated for Oregon's tourism efforts
by the 1995 legislature.
<H2>Mission Statement</H2>

<P>
It is the mission of the Travel Industry Council of Oregon to
cooperatively promote and ensure the economic vitality of Oregon's
visitor industry through leadership, advocacy, communication,
and education.
<H2>Objectives</H2>

<OL>
<LI>To provide a leadership role for the visitor industry in the
state of Oregon by communicating the economic benefits of tourism
to the people of Oregon, its governmental entities, and agencies.
<LI>To develop and implement programs which will educate all affected
audiences, public and private, of the economic value and contribution
the organization makes toward achieving its goals.
<LI>To work toward ensuring stable funding sources for the promotion
of Oregon's visitor industry.
<LI>To support and improve the balanced growth and development
of the visitor industry in Oregon.
<LI>To establish a working relationship between the State of Oregon
and the visitor industry for the promotion of tourism.
<LI>To promote and provide a forum for the exchange of information
and the discussion of tourism matters by associations and others
interested in the visitor industry.
<LI>To promote common business interests and improve business
conditions in the visitor industry.
<LI>To foster and promote public respect for the visitor industry.
</OL>
<p>


