<HEAD>

<TITLE>VIA Kit Online: Overview: The Visitor Industry Awareness Program: Purpose and Usage</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<a href="../index.htm"><img align=bottom src="../gifs/tico.gif" border=0 alt="Oregon Welcomes You!"></a>

<a href="../via.htm"><img align=bottom src="../gifs/visitor.gif" border=0 alt="Visitor Industry Awareness Campaign"></a>

<a href="viakit.htm"><img align=bottom src="../gifs/kit.gif" border=0 alt="Visitor Industry Awareness Campaign"></a>
<p>
<a href="overview.htm">Overview</a> - 
<a href="resear.htm">Research</a> - 
<a href="resource.htm">Resources</a> - 
<a href="govt.htm">Government</a> - 
<a href="medi.htm">Media Relations</a> - 
<a href="tools.htm">Tools And Ideas</a>

<br><HR>
<H1>The Visitor Industry Awareness Program: Purpose and Usage
</H1>

<H2>Purpose:</H2>

<P>
The Visitor Industry Awareness program was developed in response
to ongoing requests from industry members and tourism professionals
in Oregon for a comprehensive resource to assist them in &quot;making
a case&quot; for tourism in their communities.   The program and
this kit are designed to:
<UL>
<LI>Generate a better understanding from all target audiences
on the value of Oregon's tourism industry.
<LI>Increase or stabilize local and statewide funding for tourism
programs.
<LI>Provide an attractive, recognizable image of welcoming to
all visitors, including Oregonians.
<LI>Support the state's marketing efforts for tourism creating
increased new and repeat visits and visitor expenditures.
<LI>Provide a communication system for the tourism industry.
</UL>

<P>

<H2>Usage:</H2>

<P>
The kit is divided into various sections:  research, resources,
key influencers, media relations and tools and ideas.   Each section
provides different tools and resources and can be used in the
following ways:
<P>
1. Respond to speaking opportunities 
<UL>
<LI>use research and speech outlines.
</UL>

<P>
2. Create interest and publicity for the community, industry.
specific events and business promotions 
<UL>
<LI>use media relations section, &quot;how to's&quot; and media
lists 
<LI>use tools section - &quot;how to's&quot; and ideas
</UL>

<P>
3. Influence local, regional or state government 
<UL>
<LI>use sample support letter format
<LI>complete work sheet on local government
<LI>use legislative mailing lists
<LI>use research, sample speech outlines and talking points
</UL>

<P>
4. Launch an awareness campaign in your community
<UL>
<LI>use tools section &quot;creating a campaign&quot; which will
guide you to which tools, resources and ideas you will need for
your unique situation.
<LI>use media relations section to publicize your campaign.
<LI>use specific tools; i.e., stickers, buttons and banners to
increase visibility and enhance awareness.
</UL>

<P>

<P>
The kit has purposely been designed to be flexible.   Pull out
and use those pages from each section as the need arises.   Existing
pages can be easily substituted with updated or corrected information.
 
<P>
For further usage suggestions, see the &quot;How to Use This Section&quot;
page in each category.
<P>
Key industry members in every region of the state have been trained
to use this kit and can be helpful if you have questions.   To
learn the name of the contact person closest to you, or to give
input and suggestions for improvements to the kit contact:
<P>
Janet Porter, VIA Campaign Coordinator
<P>
P. O. Box 20057
<P>
Keizer, OR   97307
<P>
Phone: (503) 393-35335
<P>
Fax:  (503) 393-3040
</BODY>

