<HEAD>

<TITLE>VIA Kit Online: Overview: Industry Definitions</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<a href="../index.htm"><img align=bottom src="../gifs/tico.gif" border=0 alt="Oregon Welcomes You!"></a>

<a href="../via.htm"><img align=bottom src="../gifs/visitor.gif" border=0 alt="Visitor Industry Awareness Campaign"></a>

<a href="viakit.htm"><img align=bottom src="../gifs/kit.gif" border=0 alt="Visitor Industry Awareness Campaign"></a>
<p>
<a href="overview.htm">Overview</a> - 
<a href="resear.htm">Research</a> - 
<a href="resource.htm">Resources</a> - 
<a href="govt.htm">Government</a> - 
<a href="medi.htm">Media Relations</a> - 
<a href="tools.htm">Tools And Ideas</a>

<br><HR>
<H1>Industry Definitions</H1>

<H2><A NAME="_Toc339878653"></A><A NAME="_Toc340996085">TOURISM</A>
</H2>

<P>
Tourism is a composite of activities, services and industries
that deliver a travel experience, i.e., transportation, accommodations,
eating and drinking establishments, entertainment, recreation,
destination attractions, historical and cultural experiences,
shopping and other services available to travelers away from home.
<H2><A NAME="_Toc339878654"></A><A NAME="_Toc340996086">VISITORS</A>
</H2>

<P>
Those individuals traveling away from home for business or pleasure
who also seek leisure, entertainment, recreational, cultural,
historical, or retail purchasing experiences.
<P>
 
<P>
Source: Travel Industry Council of Oregon (December 1995)
<P>
