<P>
15. Do you work for a business or company that provides services
to visitors, for example a hotel, tourist attraction or retail
store?
<OL>
<LI>Yes 16%
<LI>Don't know 4%
<LI>No 80%
</OL>

<P>

<H2>16. Are you planning to visit other parts of Oregon this year
for a vacation, business or for some other reason?</H2>

<OL>
<LI>No 31%
<LI>Don't know if will visit Oregon 6%<BR>
<BR>
If yes: How many nights do you expect to be away from home traveling
in Oregon?<BR>

<LI>Yes, 0 nights 3%
<LI>Yes, 1-2 nights 16%
<LI>Yes, 3 or more nights 40%
</OL>

<P>

<H2>17. What is your approximate age?</H2>

<OL>
<LI>18-29 13%
<LI>30-44 21%
<LI>45-54 17%
<LI>55-64 18%
<LI>65+ 26%
</OL>

<P>

<H2>18. How long have you lived in Oregon?</H2>

<OL>
<LI>0-5 years 6%
<LI>6-10 years 7%
<LI>11-20 years 14%
<LI>21+ years 72%
<LI>N/A 1%
</OL>

<H2>19. Which of the following categories includes your approximate
household income?</H2>

<OL>
<LI>Less than $20,000 20%
<LI>$20,000-$29,999 13%
<LI>$30,000-$39,999 18%
<LI>$40,000-$49,999 15%
<LI>$50,000-$59,999 9%
<LI>$60,000 or more 9%
<LI>Don't know
</OL>

<H2>20. Gender</H2>

<OL>
<LI>Male 49%
<LI>Female 51%
</OL>

<P>

<H2>21. Would you describe the area where you live as urban, suburban
or rural?</H2>

<OL>
<LI>Urban 27%
<LI>Suburban 31%
<LI>Rural 40%
<LI>Don't know 2%
</OL>

<P>

<P>
Source: Moore Information (September 1995)
