<HEAD>

<TITLE>VIA Kit Online: Government: Sample Support Letter</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<a href="../index.htm"><img align=bottom src="../gifs/tico.gif" border=0 alt="Oregon Welcomes You!"></a>

<a href="../via.htm"><img align=bottom src="../gifs/visitor.gif" border=0 alt="Visitor Industry Awareness Campaign"></a>

<a href="viakit.htm"><img align=bottom src="../gifs/kit.gif" border=0 alt="Visitor Industry Awareness Campaign"></a>
<p>
<a href="overview.htm">Overview</a> - 
<a href="resear.htm">Research</a> - 
<a href="resource.htm">Resources</a> - 
<a href="govt.htm">Government</a> - 
<a href="medi.htm">Media Relations</a> - 
<a href="tools.htm">Tools And Ideas</a>

<br><HR>
<H1>Sample Support Letter</H1>

<H2>Address and salutation should be in this form:</H2>

<BR>
The Honorable John Doe
<BR>
State Capitol
<BR>
Salem, OR 97310
<BR>
Dear Senator Doe:
<H2>Your letter should clearly state the following:</H2>

<BR>
1. The issue you are writing about
<BR>
 a) Bill #
<BR>
 b) Basic Summary
<BR>
2. How you are affected by the proposed legislation
<BR>
 a) You personally (and your family)
<BR>
 b) Your community
<BR>
 c) Your industry
<BR>
3. How you want them to vote
<H2>Remember:</H2>

<UL>
<LI>The letter should be hand-written.
<LI>Use letterhead and envelope with your full name and address.
<LI>Keep it brief.
<LI>Persistence pays off!
</UL>

<BR>

<BR>
Source: Adapted by Permission from the Oregon Lodging Association
(October 1995)
<BR>
File name: LETTER.DOC
<BR>
Download this file at: <A HREF="ftp://ftp.tico.org/viakit">ftp://ftp.tico.org/viakit</A>
</BODY>

